social_posts.post_text: We’re having a son this summer y’all ❤️ (excuse my hair I was wearing a hat all day before this photoshoot 🤣).
The Rio at Boquillas Crossing on the Texas/Mexico border 🌵

Was invited by @Lincoln to attend a party in Nashville celebrating their 100 Faces of Lincoln campaign! #Ad A lovely night out with new and vintage Lincoln models to celebrate their heritage and bright/exciting future.

#LincolnNautilus #Lincoln100
2022 Lincoln Nautilus Reserve model shown with available features

Castin’ for redfish as the sun goes down with @captjongore. Been a blast getting into fly fishing - it’s something I’ve wanted to be a part of for a long time. I have no idea what I’m doing but the good times are rollin’. Thanks again to Jon and everyone down in the lowcountry for helping me out and letting me shoot with y’all. Let’s get another weekend on the books! @kevin.reif @barkeronthefly
Big Pine Key, Florida in January 2023. #leicam6
Mesa Arch at sunrise. A classic American landscape shot on #35mm
More #ektachrome from the #leicam6 in Death Valley ✨💙

I think it’s been over a year now that black and white pictures have been my favorite to look at. Photographers like @bryanschutmaat and @photodre sent me down the rabbit hole to learn about the great historical guys and gals who shot black and white. Been shooting a lot of b&w myself, but still trying to figure it out. Here’s a few from Utah on #trix400 + #leicam6

Didn’t get any photos I really liked on this trip. Plane tickets, hotels, restaurants and gas stations, film, developing - the list goes on and y’all know it all too well yourself. It’s just part of the game being one of the sickos who still shoots in this archaic way. Always wondering what you could have done different in regards to composition or with the exposures. Always wishing the weather could have been better on this night or that morning. We’ll get ‘em next time. Here’s a few random ones lightly edited, all shot on  #mamiya7 and dev + scanned at @phtsdr 💙

Samuel James Wolfenbarger, born on June 3rd. I have no idea what’s going on, but I am incredibly grateful to be along for this ride. Also thankful that momma and baby are healthy. Biggest love to all of our family and friends ❤️
Still trying to get used to my Rollei. Missed a lot of compositions on this trip, but excited nonetheless to continue my 6x6 journey after a failed relationship with the Hasselblad.
Pictures from a weekend with friends in the Outer Banks. #35mm #leicam6
